The paper discusses the use of electronic media in scholarly communication, with a focus on the differences between scientific fields. The paper also mentions the use of different communicative forums, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The discussion of the social shaping of technology and disciplinary constructions of trust suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the mention of electronic revolution and convergence suggests a focus on social and information sciences (cs.SI).
